{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UXmYXdXFMcNkohU8iRU5Kz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary\n\n### 1. What does `pnpm test:visual` do?\n\n**Root `package.json`:**\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual\"\n```\n\n**Platform `package.json`:**\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n\"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\"\n```\n\nSo `pnpm test:visual` runs Playwright visual regression tests. It's a Turbo task that delegates to the platform app's Playwright test runner.\n\n### 2. Existing visual tests\n\nThere are **two visual test suites** in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/`:\n\n- **`routes.spec.ts`** — Tests 12 route baselines (home, coinflip, lord-of-rngs, close-call, crash, game-of-trades, profile, quests, loot, fairness, leaderboard, 404)\n- **`states.spec.ts`** — Tests UI state variants (wallet connected/disconnected, tier selection, lobby navigation) covering home, profile, lord-of-rngs, and coinflip pages\n\n### 3. Architecture — Playwright-based screenshot comparison\n\n**Technology Stack:**\n- **Playwright v1.58.2** for browser automation and screenshot capture\n- **Custom `stablePage` fixture** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`) that:\n  - Seeds `Math.random()` with Mulberry32 PRNG (seed=42) for deterministic behavior\n  - Seeds `crypto.getRandomValues()` for reproducible Keypair generation\n  - Freezes `Date.now()` to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n  - Disables all CSS/SVG animations and transitions (critical for pixel-perfect snapshots)\n  - Waits for font loading and network idle\n  - Collects and fails on console errors\n\n**Configuration** (`playwright.config.ts`):\n- **Snapshot directory:** `e2e/__snapshots__/{testFilePath}/{arg}{ext}`\n- **Browser:** Chromium (Desktop)\n- **Viewport:** 1280×1080\n- **Max pixel diff threshold:** 0.015 (1.5% by default, overridable per-test)\n- **Web server:** Runs `pnpm dev` with `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` (mock wallet)\n- **Workers:** 1 (sequential)\n\n**Snapshot storage:**\nAll baselines are stored in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/` with PNG files for each test case (21 snapshots total).\n\n**Workflow:**\n- **Compare:** `pnpm test:visual` — runs tests and compares against existing snapshots\n- **Update:** `pnpm test:visual:update` — captures fresh snapshots to baseline for CI/acceptance"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a13e53a7766f7b00d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 42676\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 52436</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57012489-795c-4409-b027-2a3e1d90bed0","uuid":"91075e99-b730-40c6-88b6-ad40239942ce","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Quickly find:\n1. What does `pnpm test:visual` do? Check package.json files for `test:visual` script at root level and in `sources/rng-utopia/package.json`\n2. Are there any existing visual tests in `e2e/visual/` or `sources/rng-utopia/e2e/visual/`?\n3. What's the general structure - is this Playwright-based screenshot comparison?\n\nWorking directory: /workspaces/rng-utopia","agentId":"a13e53a7766f7b00d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary\n\n### 1. What does `pnpm test:visual` do?\n\n**Root `package.json`:**\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual\"\n```\n\n**Platform `package.json`:**\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n\"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\"\n```\n\nSo `pnpm test:visual` runs Playwright visual regression tests. It's a Turbo task that delegates to the platform app's Playwright test runner.\n\n### 2. Existing visual tests\n\nThere are **two visual test suites** in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/`:\n\n- **`routes.spec.ts`** — Tests 12 route baselines (home, coinflip, lord-of-rngs, close-call, crash, game-of-trades, profile, quests, loot, fairness, leaderboard, 404)\n- **`states.spec.ts`** — Tests UI state variants (wallet connected/disconnected, tier selection, lobby navigation) covering home, profile, lord-of-rngs, and coinflip pages\n\n### 3. Architecture — Playwright-based screenshot comparison\n\n**Technology Stack:**\n- **Playwright v1.58.2** for browser automation and screenshot capture\n- **Custom `stablePage` fixture** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`) that:\n  - Seeds `Math.random()` with Mulberry32 PRNG (seed=42) for deterministic behavior\n  - Seeds `crypto.getRandomValues()` for reproducible Keypair generation\n  - Freezes `Date.now()` to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n  - Disables all CSS/SVG animations and transitions (critical for pixel-perfect snapshots)\n  - Waits for font loading and network idle\n  - Collects and fails on console errors\n\n**Configuration** (`playwright.config.ts`):\n- **Snapshot directory:** `e2e/__snapshots__/{testFilePath}/{arg}{ext}`\n- **Browser:** Chromium (Desktop)\n- **Viewport:** 1280×1080\n- **Max pixel diff threshold:** 0.015 (1.5% by default, overridable per-test)\n- **Web server:** Runs `pnpm dev` with `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` (mock wallet)\n- **Workers:** 1 (sequential)\n\n**Snapshot storage:**\nAll baselines are stored in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/` with PNG files for each test case (21 snapshots total).\n\n**Workflow:**\n- **Compare:** `pnpm test:visual` — runs tests and compares against existing snapshots\n- **Update:** `pnpm test:visual:update` — captures fresh snapshots to baseline for CI/acceptance"}],"totalDurationMs":52436,"totalTokens":42676,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1121,"cache_read_input_tokens":40804,"output_tokens":747,"server_tool_use":{"web_